{"updated_at": "2011-11-16T07:40:23Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-11-16T07:02:18Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2756432", "id": 2756432, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505", "issue_id": 505, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/mhutchin", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "73ad07eab73d0bfaae8407926d89a5c4", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/73ad07eab73d0bfaae8407926d89a5c4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F86e78499eeb33fb9cac16b7555b50767.png", "id": 2162, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/events{/privacy}", "login": "mhutchin", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mhutchin/followers"}, "body": "I agree with @NZKoz that this should not be included before 4.0 at the earliest. Unless I'm mistaken, RFC-5789 is still just a proposed standard, and it can still be changed or retracted. See: http://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc5789\r\n\r\n@steveklabnik This isn't the way things are supposed  to work _yet_, and even without all of the recent changes, we should only implement the standard when we know it won't change or be retracted- to do otherwise would be irresponsible. PATCH has been discussed by the IETF for almost ten years, why the rush to implement it in Rails now?", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c1510120fc"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-2756432"}
